# .graphifyignore — controls what the graphify knowledge graph (graphify-out/) scans.
#
# WHY THIS FILE EXISTS: graphify reads .graphifyignore in PLACE OF .gitignore at
# this directory (it does not merge them). So this file must MIRROR .gitignore and
# then add the one extra exclusion the graph needs: the vendored editor fork.
# See docs/GRAPHIFY.md — the graph deliberately covers only OUR code + docs
# (~186 files, ~1,300 nodes); the fork is 94% of the file count and would bloat
# the graph to ~19.7k nodes. Keep it excluded on every rebuild.
#
# KEEP IN SYNC with .gitignore: if you add an entry there, add it here too.

# --- mirror of .gitignore ---
node_modules/
dist/
out/
*.log
.DS_Store
npm-debug.log*

# Cloned upstream repos used only as local research reference (not part of the app)
opensource-solutions/

# Throwaway de-risking spike (prototype only; findings captured in docs/)
spike/

# Local scheduler lock
.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock

# Oracle scratch fixtures (clone exports / Word-authored probes; never checked in)
tests/fixtures/.oracle-*
tests/fixtures/oracle-*

# Slice-4 Codex computer-use probe evidence (screenshots; never checked in)
.oracle-probes/

# Codex/agent scratch (not part of the project)
.agents/

# --- graphify-only exclusion (NOT in .gitignore — the fork is tracked code) ---
# The vendored ProseMirror engine forked from SuperDoc. Excluded from the graph
# (docs/GRAPHIFY.md). Grep it directly when you need engine internals.
src/renderer/core/superdoc-fork/
